dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Countywide DEM for Monroe County, WI 2010
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived countywide DEM (Digital Elevation Model) for Monroe County, Wisconsin in 2010. A DEM represents the bare-Earth surface, removing all natural and built features.
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
uw_supplemental_s: This lidar data dataset was created by the WisconsinView Partners (WVP) – the WI Department of Administration’s Geographic Information Office in collaboration with the UW-Madison Space Science and Engineering Center’s (SSEC) WisconsinView repository. Original lidar data in tiled format from federal or local county/city lidar projects were used to create countywide mosaics of datasets such as DEMS, Intensity images, and DSMs in various projections and coordinate systems. For detailed metadata please visit: https://web.s3.wisc.edu/wsco-wisconsinview/lidar/Monroe/Monroe_2010_County_Delivery/Metadata/Metadata.zip
